Maya Mountains, Bladen Nature Reserve. Upper Bladen Branch basin, hilltop aprox. 0.5 km south of Maya Mountain divide. Tall, semideciduous forest on summit of hill, on volcanic-derived soils. Canopy 20-30 m tall, with Euterpe, Zanthoxylum, Mimosaceae, Lauraceae spp., Euphorbiaceae spp); emergents Calophyllum, Ampelocera; understory trees: Myrcia, Guatteria, tree ferns; understory herbs and shrubs: Synecanthus, Psychotria, Danaea, Polybotrya.
